post_text:
All students will be able to enjoy a free breakfast and free lunch until December. Please do not send any money at this time. All students will order their lunch when the arrive at school. Their breakfast will be delivered to the classrooms. There will be no snacks or extras available for purchase. As for the extra meals that will be sent home for the days not present at school, that will start the week of Monday 9/14.

On the menu for the first day of school...

Turkey & Cheese Sandwich on a fresh roll or
Chicken Caesar Salad (dressing on the side) or
PB&J Sandwich.

There will be multiple options daily subject to change as there has been stock outs of lots of items. More information to follow.

Michael J Simoncini shared a post to the group: Pinelands School District Cafeteria Page.
August 17 at 11:36 AM 路

Little Egg Harbor School District
August 17 at 11:27 AM 路

Attention all Pinelands Regional School District, Little Egg Harbor School District, Tuckerton Elementary School and Eagleswood Elementary School parents:

The online free/reduced lunch application portal is now open.
https://mealapp.lunchtimesoftware.net/

Please remember, only one application is needed per family as long as your children attend one of these schools. Please also be sure you included all household members, including out of district students and non-school aged children. If you have any questions or are new to the district or are unable to submit an online application, please contact Sarah O'Toole at sotoole@lehsd.org.

*Your prior year eligibility will be available at the beginning of the school year, but is set to expire on October 20, 2020.
**A PDF version and instructions can be found on the school website. You may print and mail it to:
Little Egg Harbor School District
Attn: Sarah O'Toole
307 Frog Pond Rd.
Little Egg Harbor, NJ 08087

shared_text:
Governor Phil Murphy
August 3 at 12:11 PM 路

UPDATE: Face coverings will be required for all students at all times while inside a school building, regardless of social distancing, unless doing so would inhibit the individuals health.

The updated guidance from the New Jersey Department of Education on face coverings for students will also include several exceptions to this standard including an exception for certain students with disabilities.

Additionally, the Department is sharing its checklist of specific items that its country offices of education will use to ensure that district plans meet our guidelines.

The Department is also currently finalizing a FAQ document about reopening plans.

There has been recent reporting of a condition occurring in children called MIS-C or Multisystem Inflammatory Syndrome in Children. We do not yet know what causes MIS-C. However, we know that many children with MIS-C had the virus that causes COVID-19 or had been exposed to someone with COVID-19. MIS-C is a condition where different body parts can become inflamed, including the heart, lungs, kidneys, brain, skin, eyes or gastrointestinal organs. MIS-C can be serious, even fatal, but most ...

post_text:
Got bubbles? Today is Bubbles 4 Autism day! What better way to chase boredom and mayhem in our homes than to get out the bubbles to spread awareness.
We are all going nuts attempting to teach our kids so we need a bubbles break people!
Join us and post your videos and photos of as you spread bubbles of awareness, acceptance and hope to the skies above. wear rainbow colors or whatever is clean, just go outside! 

April is Autism Spectrum Acceptance Month! 
Rainbows are kind of our thing too 
please send up bubbles of hope to the skies above for the world. We all need a reason to smile 
#faces4autism #bubbles4autism

post_text:
UPDATE ON SCHOOL CLOSURE:

At this time, we have not received any information that would indicate we should close school due to the Covid-19 virus, however things are changing rapidly. Tuckerton Elementary School has implemented a plan to be prepared in the event that circumstances change. You may see that your child came home today with a folder/packet in their backpack (not all grades and classes) which contains instructional activities. This was sent home merely as a precaution and is only to be used when/if we close school.

We will continue to monitor the situation closely and will share out any information or updates we receive as quickly as possible. Any information about school closures will come directly from us.

Mrs. Gangemi

post_text:
Mrs. Ballin's Preschool class had some special guests today.
They started their investigation on how people make clothes by learning how a sewing machine works and making their own tooth fairy pillows (complete with tooth pockets...a feature of clothing they learned about last week).
The students used the foot pedals to run the sewing machines as the adults helped guide the material. The kids did a great job! #tespride
